The paper proposes a SAT-based approach for mining frequent flexible sequences in transactional datasets. This involves formulating and adding constraints to the model to extract more specific patterns. The use of interactive solving is also mentioned. Based on these aspects, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI, followed by cs.DB and cs.DM. The paper also involves experimentation with real datasets, which could fall under cs.LG or cs.SE.
